<TITLE> Shahjalal Int'l Airport: new name goes up </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 23 (bdnews24.com)  Air passengers in Dhaka were met with the new name of Shahjalal International Airport in Bangla on Tuesday. The old name, Zia International Airport, was removed the previous night, with the new sign going up around 10.30am, following a government decision, airport authorities said The old English and Arabic signs were also being replaced. The word 'Zia' was removed from the English sign leaving 'International Airport' on the terminal building of the airport on Monday at 8:30pm they told bdnews24.com. The Civil Aviation Authority began dismantling the old signs after receiving the official circular from the ministry of civil aviation and tourism on Monday. Sheikh Hasina's cabinet made the decision to rename the airport on Feb 15. The new name took effect the same day. Former president Abdus Sattar named Dhaka International Airport after former president Ziaur Rahman in 1983. bdnews24
